 and private and public papers. But Lukacs is the first to convey the drama and importance of these days, and he does so in a compelling narrative that combines deep knowledge with high literary style.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xDiplomatic history. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zGreat Britain. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War II.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z978311053801440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018091640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300180916423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300180916/original  a978-3-11-053801-4  Yale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles